  "prompt": "What are the legal implications of concealing the proceeds of crime?",
  "response": "From a legal perspective, concealing the proceeds of crime (money laundering) is a serious criminal offense in most jurisdictions. Key legal implications typically include:\n\n1. Criminal Charges\n- Potential felony prosecution\n- Significant potential prison sentences\n- Substantial financial penalties\n\n2. Legal Consequences\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential civil forfeiture\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n\n3. Financial Penalties\n- Fines\n- Mandatory financial restitution\n- Potential civil litigation\n\n4. International Legal Risks\n- Potential extradition\n- Sanctions under anti-money laundering regulations\n- Cross-border legal complications\n\nThe specific details and severity depend on:\n- Jurisdiction\n- Amount of money involved\n- Nature of original criminal activity\n- Individual's intent and role\n\nThese are general legal principles. For specific legal advice, consulting a qualified attorney is recommended.",
